<h1>Problem 2001 - 2024 USAMO, P2 of 6, AC</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 9</h2>
<p>Let \(S_1, S_2, \ldots, S_{100}\) be finite sets of integers whose intersection is not empty. For each non-empty \(T \subseteq \{S_1, S_2, \ldots, S_{100}\},\) the size of the intersection of the sets in \(T\) is a multiple of the number of sets in \(T\). What is the least possible number of elements that are in at least \(50\) sets?</p>
